 You do a good analisys Kanata.<br>
<br>
 As you said the game is not the same at different levels.<br>
 4 month ago the average level of BRH was 30 to 35 I think, we did raids in places like CC, Droga ...<br>
 Now our average level is 50: we do raids in planes, chardok royal ...<br>
<br>
 You can't find a group fast, you can't have fun with no well balanced group or only in place you go everyday and you are bore.<br>
<br>
 Goolak and me designed the charter for level 50+.<br>
 So those persons (50+) who are 80% of the guild, they have fun and keep like TH.<br>
 We also tried to keep the spirit of BRH at the maximum.<br>
 Both are not easy to combine, and we try our best. We are human and do errors sometimes, but I think we doing well.<br>
<br>
 Our officers are strong leaders and understand the challenges of the game at high level (or try).<br>
 Then we try to find what to do with the guild to keep the fun, the family and do not burn out everybody.<br>
<br>
 We are a collection of friends who try to have fun together and help each others.<br>
<br>
 If we take the sample of real life.<br>
 If you need to move furnitures you will need friends to help you, one day you will help them and another day they will help you.<br>
 They will understand that sometimes you can't come to help.<br>
 But if you never come to help and one day you ask they will not come.<br>
<br>
 It's the same in TH.<br>
 Let's look the way we do epics.<br>
 Do an epics help one person, but once this person have epic this will help all the guild each raids.<br>
 Today we have 5 epics in TH, to each raids you will see at least 3 epics, this allow us to do things we couldn't before.<br>
 To do an epic we need do 3 to 4 raids with 20 to 30 persons.<br>
 So one day you will come to help one friend and the day you will need this friend he will come.<br>
<br>
 In TH this is very important: if you never come to help what friend are you?<br>
 If you never come to help and one day you ask for help, you just use the guild ... this is not friendly.<br>
 <br>
 To come back to your question:<br>
 <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> If I am playing an alt instead of participating in a RED raid, for whatever reason, then am I going to be looked down upon?</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
 We are not an army so this is not Black or White. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
 For exemple:<br>
 - you play an alt of a class we need: you help the guild, and this is very hard for you because you can't play with us,<br>
 - we doing a red raid but we are enough for this, or your class will not help us more: take the time you need to do things you like,<br>
 - you did all the last raids and you need a break, this is normal everybody need break,<br>
<br>
 In the other way:<br>
 - we do a raid red we need the maximum of persons or we'll fail - if you come we can success -  you not coming and we failed on the edge - you are not helping us, and we all died just because we missed one or 2 persons,<br>
 - you never come to raids (what ever the reasons), and one day we go in a place you want loot so you come hoping for loot - you use the guild, this is not the way friends do, (we'll remove people who do like this),<br>
 - everybody is at the raid and they are in CR having difficulties, you doing great XP and you won a loot: you say in GU: waou cool I got this 20k item and and did 1 yellow today. This is not very friendly either.<br>
<br>
 The raids are one part of the guild events.<br>
 We limited the guild to level 40+ to be sure we can all play together anytime we want.<br>
 If we never see you in groups and you always do something outside of the guild we'll look down upon you.<br>
 Some class are not helped to group but we (officers) try to help you find a group most of the time (we also do break sometimes).<br>
<br>
 Maui said something that is not true for TH.<br>
<br>
 Let me give you few samples:<br>
 - we changed the charter after the release because one member didn't liked something and said it,<br>
 - for each new member every members are part of the decision, you just have to speak,<br>
 - very few decision are doen be me only, the officers act like a team,<br>
 - we inform you of a lot of thing on the private board, more than you can see in most of the guilds,<br>
 - we talk with any members who need to talk with an officer,<br>
 <br>
 TH change, TH is not BRH. Each leader make a different guild.<br>
 TH is demanding much more than BRH did, but TH provide much more than BRH (I hope).<br>
