Kanata, well you play a wizard on day basis, so I know you know what you are talking about. But I have a wizard too, and I know somethings. <br>
A Wizard that can time, is a good wizard, he won't get aggro, he won't ping pong and he will nuke for about maybe 900 to 1200 damage depending of lvl and mana, clarity etc...<br>
A wizard that times his/hers nukes don't need heals. Monks need heals, healing drains Cleric of mana, and it may result in down time. Nobody likes down time.<br>
<br>
And I will make a suggestion to all players: If you like your class, don't start an Alternate.<br>
This is of course optional, but getting higher lvl, increases the fun this game offers, and a lvl 60 Character helps ALOT more then a lvl 51 or 55 with loads of AA points, exception, <br>
